1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on resource allocation in LTE systems, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes a new power allocation method, which is related to information theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with scheduling and allocation of resources in a system, which is related to systems and control. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions Quality of Experience (QoE) which is related to multimedia applications. 
5. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper deals with resource allocation in a distributed system, which is related to distributed computing.
